article.headline: Villarroel scores 30, Schuknecht grabs 10 rebounds
article.linkText: Villarroel breaks 30-point barrier as No. 22 Oklahoma wins in Honolulu
article.story:
HONOLULU (AP) -- Maria Villarroel scored 30 points, and Theresa
Schuknecht grabbed 10 rebounds Friday night to lead Oklahoma (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today; No. 23 Associated Press) over Fordham 90-62 in the opening round of the Rainbow Wahine
Classic.

	   The Sooners (4-1) will face North Carolina (3-0; No. 12 ESPN/USA Today; No. 11 Associated Press), an
82-66 winner over DePaul, Saturday in the semifinals.

	   Villarroel was 13-for-18 from the field, relying on her speed to
make breakaway layups. Caitlin Chiaramonte had 12 points and
Mobolaji Akiode added 10 for Fordham (2-1).

	   Oklahoma shot 54 percent for the game, while making 20 of 27
free throws.

	   Dionnah Jackson added 14 points for the Sooners, and teammate
Antoinett Wadsworth had 13.

	   The Rams failed to hit any of their five 3-point shots, while
the Sooners were 4-for-15 from long range.
